column5: Enjoying some down time    Funny thing, I bought these fake fish tatoo stick on's in the city and put them on my ankle one day, then at the end of the day I had white fish spots on my legs where I had tanned around them    I got some amazing scenery and wildlife shots.  I chased this woodpecker all over camp trying to get the perfect shot    This beetle was very large and flew, ewwwwww    The pinchers of a wood beetle             Every day threatened a storm, but it just seemed to miss us, until Thursday.  We stayed out this time because everytime we came back worried about a storm, nothing happened.  This one, however, did happen, and it was a doozie.       Man did it rain.  It came down in buckets and hailed as well.  Lots of lightening and thunder.  We hid in our gazebo.    We kept 4 pike out of all the ones we caught and I cleaned them and they are sitting in the freezer at Kevin and Leslie's    So that was our week and Lakair and I want to thank Kevin and Leslie for being great hosts once again and Zach for attending to us all week, you were fantastic.  Thanks everyone for making this holiday a memorable one.  Cheers,  Joey & Tybo
Very nice photo layout and comments.
Very Cool Pics!!! That's a great shot of the Redheaded Peckerwood!!! Those beatles are great catfish bait!... and the little toadie is soooo cute!!!  Very nice Pike too!!!
Great reports folks and it was greater meeting the two of you.
Some great shots there Joey...  Maureen
Some awesome pic's Joey....  Nice to have seen you and Paul again...
Sorry I missed you guys this year. Great report and pics.
Thanks for the second set of pics. Man those woopeckers are huge and noisy. Thanks
Nice report and pics Jeoy.....Love the big woodywoodpecker pic...very cool
Great seeing you guys again Joey and nice to hear your last week went so well up there.  Your pictures turned out excellent !!
Great pics there, Joey.  Thanks for sharing.
Great photos, I have to make sure I get back up there next year.  Did you guys get the same site again?
Yes Rizzo, same site.  I like that site as its a bit higher up so if it rains, you don't get swamped and since we stay for a week, its nice to stay dry if the rains come.  Joey

It was great seeing you and Paul up there Joey!  All the reports have been awesome and yours is no exception.  Bly and I will be up there again for sure next year....we'll have to bribe someone for the babysitting part, but we'd like to spend at least 4 or 5 days there next year.  Thanks for all the laughs, conversation and your famous Jerky!!!
Great report Joey!  Love the shots, especially the woodpecker.
HEY Honey.... you weren't wearing that outfit last time I saw you.....
